OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Stan Ford
OL,5,FHe said: "I was on the twin Oerlikon
OL,6,F(anti-aircraft gun) and Fratton was
OL,7,FBombardon control ship for the
OL,8,FMulberry Harbour. And when it got to
OL,9,FNormandy took on the role for Mulberry
OL,10,Fas a guard ship.
OL,12,F"On D-Day we were on our way as an
OL,13,Fescort.
OL,15,F"I remember a notice went over the
OL,16,Ftannoy that when you were on top deck
OL,17,Ftry to avoid walking on the shore side
OL,18,Fof the ship because of snipers.
