OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Stan Ford
OL,5,F"Right through July and August we were
OL,6,Fthe guard ship and did our duties
OL,7,Fescorting hospital ships and the like.
OL,8,FAlso our ship was used for conferences
OL,9,Ffor the different forces."
OL,11,FMr Ford was on board one day in August
OL,12,Fwhen Fratton was fired on by a midget
OL,13,Fsubmarine and sunk off the Normandy
OL,14,Fcoast.
OL,16,FHe said: "I had been on guard duty on
OL,17,Fthe gun platform. Oerlikons were very
OL,18,Fcapable armaments for low-flying
OL,19,Faircraft and the like. There was a
OL,20,Fterrific explosion.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/6
